column1: Unity App Project (requires database work)
column5: I have a Unity app that needs a few updates.

column1: The app makes use of a few files on my Virtual Private Server, as well as an SQL database.
The app is essentially a product registry that presents the user with various products (ie: electronics, or clothes) from various API's (ie: Amazon API, Best Buy API, Walmart API)
We need to do the following tasks.

1) The first task is to remove a few of the product categories and add a few new ones. For example, if a user selects the "Electrnics" category, items from the "Electronics" category in Amazon are automatically presented to the user. We have too many categories and ned to remove about half.
We also need add a few new ones such as "womens clothes" and "mens clothes".

2) We need to remove the Walmart product selection and replace it with a different product API. The product API is called Brookstone, and it's available on CJ..Com. We have API access, it's pretty straight forward.
3) We need to add a “Forgot your password” link so that the user can recovery their password.
4) In the “My Items” page, we need the ability to move a disliked item to the “like” item list
5) If an item has been liked or disliked, we need to make sure it doesn’t appear to the user again.

6) On the “Find a friend” screen, we should automatically show the friends you’re following below the search box. Once you search it’ll replace the list of currently followed friends with the search results.
7) In the settings>Register Child screen, the UI is off after the registration. Specifically the logo at the top is duplicated for some reason.
We need a quick turnaround on the project, 48 hours.
The first two tasks should take around 3 hours and the remaining 5 tasks roughly 3 hours of work.

I'll give a 10 rating for good work.Categoría: Programación y TecnologíaSubcategoría: Programación de Apps. All the food delivery function, include three apps, MerchantSome people can ask – why do I need to develop my application if there are already aggregators or popular services which I can use? Let's check out three categories of businesses that should consider developing a food delivery service:

column1: Restaurant Chains: Owners of a large food restaurant chain across the city or country that don't want to pay an extra fee to some aggregator app.
Entrepreneurs of a Specific Area: The location they live in is too small or distant for such aggregators like UberEats, or they can't launch due to some legal issues.
Startups: Those who want to be ahead of direct competitors and by creating a food delivery service – increase the client's loyalty and break new ground.
Types of Food Delivery Apps

Business models of food ordering platforms can adjust according to business goals and requirements. Food delivery service can be local or even worldwide, giving multiple opportunities to start or extend the existing business.
